ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
CONFIGURATION SECTION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'INPUT.DAT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'OUTPUT.DAT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE.
01  INPUT-RECORD PIC X(80).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(80).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-EOF-FLAG PIC X VALUE 'N'.
    88  EOF-REACHED VALUE 'Y'.
01  WS-RECORD-COUNT PIC 9(5) VALUE 0.
01  WS-TEMP-VARIABLE PIC X(80).
01  WS-WEATHER PIC X(10) VALUE 'SUNNY'.
01  WS-UNUSED-VAR PIC X(10) VALUE 'RAINY'.

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PARA.
    PERFORM INITIALIZE
    PERFORM PROCESS-FILE
    PERFORM TERMINATE
    STOP RUN.

INITIALIZE.
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE
    DISPLAY 'Simple Text Editor Initialized'.

PROCESS-FILE.
    PERFORM UNTIL EOF-REACHED
     READ INPUT-FILE INTO WS-TEMP-VARIABLE
         AT END
          SET EOF-REACHED TO TRUE
     NOT AT END
         ADD 1 TO WS-RECORD-COUNT
         MOVE WS-TEMP-VARIABLE TO OUTPUT-RECORD
         WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD
    END-PERFORM.

TERMINATE.
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE
    DISPLAY 'Simple Text Editor Terminated'
    DISPLAY 'Total Records Processed: ' WS-RECORD-COUNT.

